The paper deals with the problem of Android malware detection, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed approach involves the use of machine learning, specifically ensemble learning, to improve detection accuracy, which suggests the relevance of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of a large repository of malware samples and benign apps, indicating the potential relevance of software engineering (cs.SE) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories.
